text: There have been too much of formulaic comedy now. This was a breath of fresh air and a blast from the past all in one. It stayed pretty true to the original Zombieland feeling   This is a sequel for fans of the first 'Zombieland', simple as that. It's not here to try and persuade mainstream critics into actually liking a Horror movie, not to make a statement on society, or give you a glimpse into the director and/or writers' state of mind. It's here to say, "Sorry we kept you all waiting, now let's get back to business!" That business being zombie gore, gross-out gags, cheesy one-liners, and jokes about men who drive minivans.

text: Night of The Wild: Animal Apocalypse is a upcoming 2021 American natural apocalyptic horror-comedy film directed by Ruben Fleischer and written by Rhett Reese and Paul Wernick.   The film stars Will Ferrell, Adam Scott, Chris Rock, John C. Reilly, Jack Nicholson, Tim Allen, Woody Harrelson, Tom Hanks and Jack Black.  The film is scheduled to be released on October 18th, 2019 in the United States and Canada, with a October 25th, 2021 release date in the Philippines and Australia.  Premise  Two years after the events of the first film, the Earth is in complete abandoned ruin as Will Ferrell, Adam Scott, John C. Reilly and Chris Rock go on a action-packed adventure to freedom with four eccentrically friendly gun-toting animal-slaving survivors as they battle, shoot and kill many of the new species of mutant animals, including ones that have evolved into genetically modified monsters, zombie animals created by the recent spreading of the toxic waste, twisted animal monster hybrids created by a gang of mad scientists called The AVD, a giant genetically engineered zombie Tyrannosaurus rex hybrid known as Agent 4783 and demonic versions of the animals in order to save themselves from permanent extinction.

text: We are the masters of a power driven to the far reaches of the universe, and we have but one desire! Can one such as you possibly fathom how dearly we have clung to this dream across the aeons? How could you! You couldn’t! Never ever ever! We who once faced those who were in such fear of our power that they sealed us away and banished us to the edge of the galaxy! US! As if THAT loveliness wasn’t enough, they tried to erase our very existence from history! RUDE! Only through our magic were we able to overcome their science and achieve great prosperity! We alone were responsible for stopping that repulsive nightmare of a galactic crisis, yet this is how you repay us! This won’t stand! It won’t be forgiven! It won’t be forgotten! Never ever EVER! Those who called us mad, are you listening? You left us at the edge of the galaxy to be forgotten, then went along your merry way, probably living somewhere pretty and peaceful! But know this! Your future is a farce! You have none! We, masters of a matter most dark, vow to be restored, as foretold in the book of legend, which everyone thought was just a fairy tale! It WASN’T! We have already obtained the vessel that contains our Dark Lord, and he will soon awaken and shower us in compassion! Look! The vessel of our Dark Lord is filling up even as we speak! Now the time for his greatness to enter our world has come! Welcome to a new history! A new age! The age of awesome! HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DARK LORD! HAPPY BIRTHDAY!

text: Okay I am very happy that this is happening obviously I am happy however however however however however I have to express my concern now that the trailer is out I have to express some concern. This is a sequel to a ten year old movie that was quietly announced months ago and only acknowledged again a couple days before the first trailer and is set to be released in just around two and a half months... should I be worried? I don't necessarily doubt that this will be a good movie far from it and I also I'm sure that there was a lot of pre-production so I expect a solid script as well as good presentation because I doubt this takes that much budget like you could this with just over a million but still for this to sort of come out of nowhere being made in what feels like a year or less and is being released so soon after it's official promotional material has been released and not to mention again he made a full decade after its previous title and well after the zombie media craze of the late 00s early 10s has passed, the one that Zombieland was basically made as both a spoof and authentic part of.... it feels real late to make a sequel yes I've wanted to sequel sure the original stands on its own but there is wiggle room and potential for more stories with these characters and I have always wanted one if only one... but you can see my concern here not necessarily for the quality of the product but of its chances at the market of the day... just all these circumstances I've noticed surrounding it gives me reason to think that this was just a case of producers sitting on an IP for so long and sorta having an opportunity to use it although they're not really interested. That this is being made just to fill out a schedule... to release a movie on a date because we need to have a movie released at this point in the year. Just mild concerns
